== Spanish ==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[caprone]]'', a form of ''[[capra]]''

=== Noun ===
'''cabrón''' [ka.ˈbɾoŋ]
plural: ''cabrones'', feminine: ''cabrona, cabronas''

# Someone who does bad things or is a bad person.
# A man whose woman is unfaithful.
# Someone who cowardly takes insults without objection.
# (Cuba, Guatemala) An astute and intelligent person. 
# A male [[goat]].

This word is generally considered [[vulgar]].

